>[Question]
>There are 10 marbles in a bag ... 2 reds, 4 greens and 4 blue. What 
is
>the probability of drawing a red, and then a green, and then a blue
>... in that exact order? "No problem," thinks I. "Just multiply 
2/10 x
>4/9 x 4/8." 
>
>But then they ask what the probability would be if the order did not
>matter. I suspect that the probability would be higher, but I am "in
>over my head" on this one.

If order does not matter

                 C(2,1) x C(4,1) x C(4,1)
  Probability =  ------------------------
                       C(10,3)

                   2 x 4 x 4      32       4
               =  ----------   = ----  =  ----
                     120         120       15


